Enhancing the Outcome Reward-based RL Training
 of MLLMswith Self-Consistency Sampling

The topic of enhancing the outcome reward-based RL training of MLLMs with self-consistency sampling is an area of ongoing research, with several papers and studies exploring the application of this approach to improve the performance and robustness of MLLMs. The use of self-consistency sampling and RL can help to reduce the gap between the model's performance in the training environment and its performance in real-world scenarios, making it a promising area of research for improving the outcome of MLLMs.
